# Coding Patterns

## Component Structure
- Client components: `'use client'` at top, named export (`export const ComponentName`)
- Props: define interface above component (`interface ComponentNameProps {}`)
- Hooks at top of component, handlers next, return last
- One component per file (exception: small helper components used only in that file)

## Styling
- Use Tailwind for layout/spacing/color, Ant Design components for interactive UI
- Don't mix inline `style={{}}` with Tailwind — prefer Tailwind
- Card pattern: `className="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm p-6"`
- No glassmorphism (no backdrop-blur, no bg-white/60, no shadow-xl shadow-slate-200/50)
- Color palette: teal-600 primary, slate-900 text, slate-500 secondary, slate-50 backgrounds

## Ant Design Usage
- Import from 'antd': `import { Card, Button, Table } from 'antd'`
- Theme overrides go in `src/theme/themeConfig.ts`, not inline
- Use Ant's `Form`, `Table`, `Select`, `Modal` — don't rebuild these
- Icons: use `lucide-react` (already installed), not Ant icons

## API Routes
```typescript
// Always this pattern:
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  try {
    const body = await request.json();
    // ... logic
    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, data });
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('[route-name]', error);
    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: 'message' }, { status: 500 });
  }
}
```

## Error Handling
- API routes: try/catch with console.error + structured error response
- Client components: try/catch in async handlers, show user-facing message via Ant `message` or `notification`
- Log with context: `console.error('[component_id]', { ts: new Date().toISOString(), error })`

## Performance
- Use `'use client'` only when needed (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
- Prefer server components for static/data-fetching pages
- Debounce user inputs (300ms) — already implemented in ProductInputSection pattern
- Don't fetch in useEffect if you can use server components or route handlers
